<br>
On my first raid (yes, the old one is reminiscing now), I was only level 39 (I was leading it, so couldn't not go for level). I was feared almost constantly, even with higher than a 70 magic resist. The next dragon raid I was 40, and just the difference in one level meant my time being feared was cut in half. The more levels I got, the easier it was to resist the fear, especially if I kept my magic resist up. By the time I was 49, I'd have fights in which I was feared for less than 1 second only once during the battle. <br>
<br>
Resists are everything if you aren't the main tank. <p>Haemish MacLennan<br>
